test_presence_of_duplicates_in_result:
assert (3 == 3 and 3 == 3 and 2 == 3)
 +  where 3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x778d0f23de00>([4])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x778d0f23de00> = [[1, 4], [1, 4, 1], [1, 4, 1], [1, 4, 1, 4], [1, 4, 1, 4], [1, 4, 1, 4, 1], ...].count
 +  and   3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x778d0f23de00>([1, 4])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x778d0f23de00> = [[1, 4], [1, 4, 1], [1, 4, 1], [1, 4, 1, 4], [1, 4, 1, 4], [1, 4, 1, 4, 1], ...].count
 +  and   2 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x778d0f23de00>([4, 1])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x778d0f23de00> = [[1, 4], [1, 4, 1], [1, 4, 1], [1, 4, 1, 4], [1, 4, 1, 4], [1, 4, 1, 4, 1], ...].count
test_if_sublist_product_equals_number:
assert 8 == 4
 +  where 8 = <built-in function prod>([4, 1, 2])
 +    where <built-in function prod> = math.prod
